values: October 5, 2002 Lucius went looking for a good restaurant. He ended up meeting with a rather annoying Weasley and having a less-than-pleasant disucssion-- though he got a restaurant recommendation out of it. October 13, 2002 Finally ready, Lucius returns to the Malfoy Manor to bring Narcissa to Annwn. After a jeweled gift, and the promise of seeing her son again, the pair head back to Annwn to their new home. October 19, 2002 Lucius runs into a 'member of the family' out at night. He and Sirius have a long discussion about this and that and getting frustrated at each other before going their separate ways. October 25, 2002 Lucius receives a strange invitation. October 26, 2002 Lucius sends an Owl to a Healer. They meet to have a discussion about the problems plaguing the Malfoy family, though not all of them. October 29, 2002 Lucius pays a visit to Severus' apothecary. Somewhat distressed at Severus' choice of an 'acceptable assistant', he manages to have a conversation with Severus, getting the man to say exactly what he was looking for. October 31, 2002 Lucius attends the Feast. He meets with his son and has a discussion. Then he speaks with Sirius Black and surprisingly does not have the urge to kill him. The Announcement makes Lucius upset. He will have to think of a plan to keep his family together, which may involve the murder of others.

Lucius entered Annwn, following strict instructions. His progeny had to be checked in on. September 29, 2002 Lucius went to Draco's home to have a talk with his son. The awkwardness was both expected and familiar-- there was much both sides could have said that they didn't. After all, what's the point of saying what's unnecessary? After the talk with Draco, Lucius retired to his new home in Annwn. He had many things to think on, to do-- but the day had been tiring already. September 30, 2002 Hunting down the Apothecary Draco mentioned in their conversation, Lucius ran into an old acquaintance. After buying a cauldron from Severus, Lucius found out very little he needed to know but decided to end the discussion for today. The conversation with Severus left Lucius wanting something to calm himself. The subsequent discussion with the young Tracey Davis both intrigued and amused Lucius, more than he'd felt since entering Annwn. He looks forward to talking to her again.
